The President of the United States sent his best wishes to the people of India on their Republic Day. He mentioned that the United States and India are the world's two largest democracies and share the belief in the potential and dignity of every human being. The President also acknowledged the contributions of the nearly three million Americans of Indian descent who enrich American society. He emphasized that the U.S-India relationship is a defining partnership of the 21st century and expressed hope for a future of greater prosperity and opportunity for both countries.